Social Media | Mobile | Email | Media | Technology | Web Design | et al.</description><title>Notes from the Field</title><generator>Tumblr (3.0; @beckyrecommends)</generator><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/</link><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/beckyrecommends" /><feedburner:info uri="beckyrecommends" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/" /><atom10:link xmlns:atom10="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" rel="hub" href="http://tumblr.superfeedr.com/" /><feedburner:browserFriendly></feedburner:browserFriendly><item><title>2011 Retail Customer Experience Top 100</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.retailcustomerexperience.com/whitepapers/intro/3628/2011-Retail-Customer-Experience-Top-100"&gt;2011 Retail Customer Experience Top 100&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;You do have to register to download this document, but it’s free and there’s a lot of good information in it.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/2623662841</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/2623662841</guid><pubDate>Thu, 06 Jan 2011 09:18:57 -0600</pubDate><category>retail</category><category>customer</category><category>marketing</category></item><item><title>Retail Ad Circulars Reveal Top Marketing Trends </title><description>&lt;a href="http://supermarketnews.com/viewpoints/marketing-trends-0103/?cid=upd"&gt;Retail Ad Circulars Reveal Top Marketing Trends &lt;/a&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/2609490572</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/2609490572</guid><pubDate>Wed, 05 Jan 2011 08:56:31 -0600</pubDate><category>retail</category><category>circular</category><category>ad</category><category>grocery</category><category>supermarket</category></item><item><title>Walmart Gets Its Groupon but Does Not Let Shoppers Dictate Deals </title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.fastcompany.com/1699296/walmart-apes-groupon-subverts-the-whole-make-retailers-drop-prices-game"&gt;Walmart Gets Its Groupon but Does Not Let Shoppers Dictate Deals &lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;This is a really interesting approach to gaining a fan base. They have a special &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.facebook.com/?ref=logo#!/walmart?v=app_140539435973047"&gt;Crowdsaver tab&lt;/a&gt; setup on their Facebook page with a weekly deal that only becomes active if a certain number of people “Like” it. You have to “Like” their page to “Like” the deal, which is how their gaining fans for their page. If they reach the threshold for number of “Likes” then the deal becomes active for &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;everyone &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;- not just those who hit the “Like” button. PLUS, visitors can “Share” the deal on their Facebook page AND when they hit “Like” can share on their Facebook page that they did so.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1454881773</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1454881773</guid><pubDate>Mon, 01 Nov 2010 13:57:16 -0500</pubDate><category>walmart</category><category>groupon</category><category>deal</category><category>facebook</category><category>tab</category><category>custom</category><category>shopping</category><category>crowdsource</category></item><item><title>Multichannel Shopping Key for Holiday Season</title><description>&lt;img src="http://28.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lb23glH0pu1qdukcfo1_400.gif"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;img src="http://28.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lb23glH0pu1qdukcfo2_400.gif"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;Multichannel Shopping Key for Holiday Season&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1431929822</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1431929822</guid><pubDate>Fri, 29 Oct 2010 09:41:09 -0500</pubDate><category>shopping</category><category>online</category><category>research</category><category>ecommerce</category><category>instore</category><category>retail</category><category>holiday</category></item><item><title>Smart, Rich, Responsible People Love Coupons</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.marketingpilgrim.com/2010/10/smart-rich-responsible-people-love-coupons.html"&gt;Smart, Rich, Responsible People Love Coupons&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;Just another reason we all need to stop making assumptions about consumers. They’re not always who we think they are. Here are some bullet points from the article…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;People who consider the environment of utmost importance are the most likely to be coupon lovers – 37% more likely than others.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;College-educated people are 78% more likely than the non-college educated to be coupon lovers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parents are 48% more likely than non-parents to be coupon lovers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The middle-aged are more likely than younger generations to have a strong opinion about online coupons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coupon lovers are 220% more likely than abstainers to highly value tradition, and 96% more likely to highly value self-direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Devoutly religious people are 31% more likely to be coupon lovers and substantially less likely to be coupon abstainers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1414939351</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1414939351</guid><pubDate>Wed, 27 Oct 2010 08:06:43 -0500</pubDate><category>coupons</category><category>saving</category></item><item><title>Mobile Ad Spending Up Nearly 80% in 2010</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article.aspx?R=1007992"&gt;Mobile Ad Spending Up Nearly 80% in 2010&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;Here are some other mobile statistics I heard at a conference this week:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;US Population is 306 M&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mobile Phone Penetration is 276 M (90% of US population)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smartphones with Internet is 69 M (25% of the US population)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In 2013, more than half of web traffic will come from mobile phones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1354426050</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1354426050</guid><pubDate>Tue, 19 Oct 2010 18:35:54 -0500</pubDate><category>mobile</category></item><item><title>Blog Marketing to Moms Is About More Than Parenting</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article.aspx?R=1007976"&gt;Blog Marketing to Moms Is About More Than Parenting&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;I’ve heard some comments recently about the “mommy blogger” trend dying out. I wouldn’t count on that. The hype around it may be declining, but those mommies aren’t going anywhere. Also just as important, 17 million moms READ blogs. So even if the number of women blogging should decline or level off, the number of women those bloggers can engage with is expected to increase to 21 million by 2014. That’s 63% of all online moms. &lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1303808449</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1303808449</guid><pubDate>Tue, 12 Oct 2010 23:23:50 -0500</pubDate><category>moms</category><category>bloggers</category><category>blogging</category><category>parenting</category><category>blog readers</category></item><item><title>Forty Percent of Groupon Merchants Say Never Again</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.marketingpilgrim.com/2010/10/forty-percent-of-groupon-merchants-say-never-again.html"&gt;Forty Percent of Groupon Merchants Say Never Again&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;Groupon can be a fantastic option for marketers, but it’s certainly not something to jump into with 40% of merchants saying it was unsuccessful for them.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1242550006</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1242550006</guid><pubDate>Mon, 04 Oct 2010 09:07:19 -0500</pubDate><category>groupon</category><category>drawbacks</category></item><item><title>Strikin' It Rich - The Mobile Rich Media Revolution</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.clickz.com/clickz/column/1734161/strikin-it-rich-the-mobile-rich-media-revolution?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+ClickZExperts+%28ClickZ+Experts%29&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader"&gt;Strikin' It Rich - The Mobile Rich Media Revolution&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;This article includes a great selection of rich media ads that provide a great view of what’s possible and what the future of mobile advertising looks like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;PREVIEW: “I&lt;span class="Apple-style-span"&gt;&lt;span class="Apple-style-span"&gt;t’s no secret that mobile advertising is growing significantly, fueled by smartphone proliferation and a corresponding increase in mobile Web usage. This growth, combined with new device capabilities, is fundamentally changing media consumption – and it’s much bigger than just being able to access the Web while on the go. A recent study indicated that nearly 40 percent of time spent on the mobile Web happens&lt;span class="Apple-converted-space"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;in the home, where presumably people have access to a computer with full keyboard and larger screen. Yet, they are choosing to turn to the phone.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1163310486</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1163310486</guid><pubDate>Tue, 21 Sep 2010 16:47:02 -0500</pubDate><category>mobile</category><category>ads</category><category>iads</category><category>apple</category><category>rich media</category></item><item><title>Best Practices in Digital Shopper Marketing</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.instoremarketer.org/files/10ISM_CDM_CatapultPaper.pdf"&gt;Best Practices in Digital Shopper Marketing&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;The findings of this study are outstanding and highly applicable to our business. I recommend that anyone that creates proposals for clients/prospects spend some time with it. When I have some “spare time” I will post some of the items that stand out to me the most, but for now I recommend at the very least you review the charts on pages 6 through 9. Great stuff!&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1129911953</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1129911953</guid><pubDate>Wed, 15 Sep 2010 21:58:00 -0500</pubDate><category>digital</category><category>marketing</category><category>in home</category><category>on the go</category><category>in store</category><category>technology</category></item><item><title>The Future of Ad Agencies and Social Media</title><description>&lt;a href="http://mashable.com/2010/09/07/future-ad-agencies-social-media/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+Mashable+%28Mashable%29"&gt;The Future of Ad Agencies and Social Media&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Great post from Mashable…&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To keep up with ever-changing advertising and marketing options, ad agencies are rapidly adopting new strategies and outlooks on how consumers interact with brands. While many ad agencies have been slow to adopt social media, others have been keeping up with the trends quite well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We talked with five people who are familiar with the connected worlds of digital media and ad agencies, and here’s what they had to say about the future of social media and advertising.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Software Is the New Medium&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Groups and Friends: The Power of the Hive Mind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transparency Is Still a Long Way Off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Location Campaigns Are the New Targeting Mechanism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display Ads Are Evolving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1089697704</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1089697704</guid><pubDate>Wed, 08 Sep 2010 22:13:02 -0500</pubDate><category>social media</category><category>software</category><category>location based services</category><category>transparency</category><category>display</category><category>social media</category><category>advertising</category><category>influence</category></item><item><title>QR Codes Help Consumer Shop for Wines
Bottles of wine will have...</title><description>&lt;img src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l8382xeXef1qdukcfo1_400.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://mashable.com/2010/09/01/cellar-key/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+Mashable+%28Mashable%29"&gt;QR Codes Help Consumer Shop for Wines&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bottles of wine will have neck tags with a QR code on them. Once scanned the code will direct consumers to details about the bottle wine and how to pair it with food.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1049709519</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1049709519</guid><pubDate>Wed, 01 Sep 2010 16:37:45 -0500</pubDate><category>wine</category><category>grocery</category><category>QR codes</category></item><item><title>Digitalization of Grocery Shopping</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.clickz.com/clickz/column/1729259/digitalization-grocery-shopping"&gt;Digitalization of Grocery Shopping&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;The author talks about three different technologies that will change the way we shop for groceries. The most interesting is from Modiv Media which is a PDA that attaches to the cart. It connects to the stores loyalty program so it knows your past purchases and preferences. It also knows where you’re at in the store so it can help you to find items on your list. Plus, as past technology has done, you scan items as you go so you never have to go through a checkout line.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020372203</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020372203</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 11:29:48 -0500</pubDate><category>grocery</category><category>supermarkets</category><category>digital</category><category>shopping</category><category>technology</category></item><item><title>Grocery Shoppers Hungry for Mobile Info
“Food-focused...</title><description>&lt;img src="http://26.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l7thvjVlPl1qdukcfo1_400.gif"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="big_red_text_multiline" id="ctl00_EMarketerContentPH_lblTitle"&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article.aspx?R=1007889"&gt;Grocery Shoppers Hungry for Mobile Info&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span class="big_red_text_multiline"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“&lt;/strong&gt;Food-focused mobile marketing often centers around coupons and promotions, but consumers are hungry for more than just discounts. They’re also looking for information.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020159411</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020159411</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 10:33:19 -0500</pubDate><category>grocery</category><category>food</category><category>supermarkets</category><category>mobile</category></item><item><title>These are from an eMarketers articles titled Nearly...</title><description>&lt;img src="http://24.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l7tg2s7QSH1qdukcfo1_400.gif"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;img src="http://27.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l7tg2s7QSH1qdukcfo2_400.gif"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;These are from an eMarketers articles titled &lt;span class="big_red_text_multiline" id="ctl00_EMarketerContentPH_lblTitle"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" href="http://www.emarketer.com/Article.aspx?R=1007894"&gt;Nearly Three-Quarters of Marketers Have Social Strategy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="big_red_text_multiline"&gt;&lt;em&gt;“Companies in the King Fish survey were divided on where the budget for social initiatives would come from, however. While 35% thought that funds would be allocated to a specific custom project, 33% said their company would increase marketing expenditures to focus more on social media.”&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020015892</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1020015892</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 09:54:28 -0500</pubDate><category>social media</category><category>budgets</category><category>strategy</category></item><item><title>Thought this was just too funny not to share. This is a t-shirt...</title><description>&lt;img src="http://28.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l7te5c5PXf1qdukcfo1_500.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thought this was just too funny not to share. This is a t-shirt they sell on a website called &lt;a href="http://www.Despair.com" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.Despair.com" target="_blank"&gt;www.Despair.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. The tagline reads, “Clothes make the man. These clothes make the man sad.”&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1019863448</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1019863448</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 09:12:00 -0500</pubDate><category>social media</category><category>myspace</category><category>facebook</category><category>twitter</category><category>foursquare</category><category>tshirt</category><category>venn diagram</category></item><item><title>The Interactive Future of Food</title><description>&lt;img src="http://30.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l7tcbf8SSo1qdukcfo1_500.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Interactive Future of Food&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1019720636</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1019720636</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Aug 2010 08:33:15 -0500</pubDate></item><item><title>Top 5 Ways Big Brands are Using Foursquare</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.mashable.com/2010/08/24/big-brands-foursquare/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed%3A+Mashable+%28Mashable%29"&gt;Top 5 Ways Big Brands are Using Foursquare&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;p&gt;Just to give everyone an idea of some ways the location based services (LBS) are being used. The growth in this area has been tremendous and those who use it are getting a lot of attention for it.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1016396670</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1016396670</guid><pubDate>Thu, 26 Aug 2010 17:34:00 -0500</pubDate><category>foursquare</category><category>location based apps</category><category>apps</category></item><item><title>Top 5 Mobile Advertising Trends To Watch</title><description>&lt;a href="http://www.mashable.com/2010/08/19/mobile-advertising-trends/"&gt;Top 5 Mobile Advertising Trends To Watch&lt;/a&gt;</description><link>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1016386541</link><guid>http://beckyrecommends.tumblr.com/post/1016386541</guid><pubDate>Thu, 26 Aug 2010 17:32:00 -0500</pubDate><category>mobile</category><category>trends</category></item></channel></rss>
